drh added on 2018-10-03 23:10:33:
The ALTER TABLE statement in the following script returns an error:
CREATE TABLE t1(a);
CREATE TABLE t2(b);
CREATE TRIGGER r1 AFTER INSERT ON t2 BEGIN
  INSERT INTO t1(a) VALUES(99);
END;
DROP TABLE t1;
ALTER TABLE t2 RENAME TO t3;
The DROP TABLE removes the table t1, which leaves a dangling reference to t1
in the trigger.  Then during the ALTER TABLE, the trigger is reparsed, but the
reparse fails due to the dangling reference.
drh added on 2019-06-10 18:51:37:
Use the "PRAGMA legacy_alter_table=ON" command to work around this if
it ever causes a problem.
